## Step 3: Start with 3 High‑Value AIOps Use Cases

Don’t turn on every feature at once. Pick a few use cases that directly attack your worst toil. [web:302][web:304][web:308][web:311][web:312]

### Use Case 1: Alert Noise Reduction and Correlation

Goal: fewer, better alerts. [web:300][web:302][web:304][web:308]

Capabilities:

- Deduplication:
  - Combine identical or near‑identical alerts.
- Correlation:
  - Group alerts from different systems into one incident based on time, topology, or symptoms. [web:304][web:308][web:311]
- Dynamic thresholds:
  - Use baselines instead of static thresholds to reduce false positives. [web:304][web:311]

Outcome to track:

- Alerts per shift.
- % of alerts that lead to action.
- Time spent triaging vs fixing. [web:300][web:302][web:304][web:308][web:307]

### Use Case 2: Faster Root Cause Analysis (RCA)

Goal: get to “what’s really broken” quicker. [web:301][web:302][web:304][web:308][web:311]

Capabilities:

- Anomaly detection:
  - Spot unusual metric/log patterns without hand‑built rules. [web:304][web:311]
- Correlated symptoms:
  - Highlight which metrics/logs changed together when the incident started. [web:308][web:311]
- Similar incident search:
  - “This looks like the outage from last March” with linked runbooks. [web:308][web:311][web:307]

Outcome to track:

- Time from first alert to plausible root cause.
- Time wasted browsing dashboards with no clear signal. [web:302][web:304][web:308]

### Use Case 3: Auto‑Resolution of Repetitive Fixes

Goal: automate well‑understood, low‑risk fixes. [web:302][web:304][web:308][web:307][web:310][web:312]

Examples:

- Restarting a known flaky service.
- Clearing a specific stuck queue.
- Scaling a worker pool under known safe bounds. [web:308][web:311][web:310]

Pattern:

- Detect pattern → map to known runbook → automate via script/infra‑as‑code → gate with safety checks. [web:302][web:304][web:308][web:307][web:312]

Outcome to track:

- # of incidents auto‑resolved.
- Reduction in wake‑up pages for known issues. [web:302][web:308][web:307]

